						               													<description>The game shows Europe as it was back in the late 1980's. All the independent states of the time are shown on the board as their flags as a way to identify them, and as geographically correct in relation to each other as possible; each flag also exists as a game card. Each player gets their &amp;quot;own&amp;quot; random country in the beginning to start from, and the idea of the game is to try to gather as many different flags for yourself as possible; players move on the board using colour-dies and a right combination of colours allows a player to turn one of the flag cards - they are shuffled on the table face down, forming a memory game element - hoping for the flag of the country they're currently standing on, or at least a flag of same colours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Flags are scored at the end of the game with the Finnish flag and each player's &amp;quot;own&amp;quot; flag carrying bonus points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One of the last original Paletti publications; the brand ceased to exist soon after, and most of it's games were taken over by Peliko.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
